parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.

parse: Verb - Perfect Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
Or neuter pleion, or pleon comparative of polus; more in quantity, number, or quality; also the major portion.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A priest, one who offers sacrifice to a god (in Jewish and pagan religions; of Christians only met.). From hieros; a priest.
A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through.
Death, physical or spiritual. From thnesko; death.

parse: Verb - Present Infinitive Middle or Passive
str2: To prevent, debar, hinder; with infin: from doing so and so. From the base of kolazo; to estop, i.e. Prevent.
To remain by, abide with; met: I persevere in. From para and meno; to stay near, i.e. Remain.
